  "grammarExplanation": "When both an indirect AND direct object pronoun appear together, the indirect one comes FIRST:\n\n• le/les + lo/la/los/las → 'se' replaces le/les\n• 'Le doy el libro' + 'lo' → 'Se lo doy' (I give it to her)\n\nWith infinitives, pronouns can attach to the end:\n• 'Se lo quiero dar' or 'Quiero dárselo'\n\nOrder: se → te/me/nos → lo/la/los/las → verb."
